Module nl.naturalis.common
Package nl.naturalis.common.check

Class IntCheck<E extends Exception>

java.lang.Object
nl.naturalis.common.check.IntCheck<E>
Type Parameters:
E - The type of the exception throw if the value does not pass the test
public final class IntCheck<E extends Exception> extends Object
Facilitates the validation of int values. See the package description for a detailed explanation.

    • ok

      public <P, F extends Throwable> P ok(ThrowingIntFunction<P,F> transformer) throws F
      Passes the argument to the specified Function and returns the value it computes. To be used as the last call after a chain of checks. For example: 
      
 int age = Check.that(person).has(Person::getAge, "age", lt(), 50).ok(Person::getAge);
      Type Parameters:
      P - The type of the returned value
      Parameters:
      transformer - A Function that transforms the argument into some other value
      Returns:
      The value computed by the Function
      Throws:
      F - The exception potentially thrown by the Function

    • is

      public IntCheck<E> is(IntPredicate test, String message, Object... msgArgs) throws E
      Validates the argument using the specified test. Allows you to provide a custom error message. See the package description for how to specify a custom error message.
      Parameters:
      test - The test
      message - The message pattern
      msgArgs - The message arguments. If you expect the argument to fail the test very often, and performance is of the utmost importance, specify exactly one message argument: '\0' (the NULL character). This will cause the message not to be parsed, and simply be passed as-is to the exception. (Of course, the message cannot contain any message arguments then.)
      Returns:
      This instance
      Throws:
      E - If the argument is invalid
